text: Guilty as ChargedWhy is it so hard for me to find joy these days  Why is it so hard for me to find hope these days Each passing moment is both dull and numb  The only feelings that I feel consistently these days are anxiety  anger  fear  misery  and most abundantly  hopelessness It s hard to feel anything when you re standing in a room that s pitch black As I wander around in the dark aimlessly  I lose hope that a light will turn on  Instead  I trip and fall  I tumble in the darkness   Each passing moment brings along with it more pain and more suffering  Tiny disasters piece together into a quilt of depression   When will this end Can I just end it myself  I used to think suicide was a selfish thing  I used to enrage at the idea that someone could think so little about the ones they loved I understand now A feeling I never thought I would feel from my depression was guilt  It s interesting how much you want people to notice your suffering  but also how much guilt you feel when they feel your misery  I don t want the people I love to feel my sadness  but I really can t do anything about it   What do you do when you feel like you re hurting the ones around you by being uncontrollably depressed
